      <p class="container-text"><span class="span-inicial">Harry Potter</span> is a series of fantasy novels written by the British author
        <span>J. K. Rowling</span>, in which the adventures of the young apprentice of magic and sorcery are described
         <span>Harry Potter</span> and his friends <span>Hermione Granger</span> y <span>Ron
          Weasley</span>, during the years spent in college <span>Hogwarts of Witchcraft and Wizardry</span>. The plot focuses on the fight between Harry Potter and the evil wizard
           <span>Lord Voldemort</span>, who murdered Harry's parents in his quest to conquer the wizarding world. <br>
           Since the release of the first novel, <span>harry potter and the Philosopher's Stone</span> In 1997, the series achieved immense popularity, critical acclaim, and commercial success around the world. By July 2013 they had been sold between
           <span>400 and 500 million copies</span> of the seven books, which ranks as the book series <span>best-selling in history</span> and which have been translated into<span>more than 65 languages
           </span>, including Latin and ancient Greek. The seventh and last book, <span>Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows</span>, was released worldwide in English on July 21, 2007, while in Spanish it was published on February 21, 2008.
           <br>
           The success of the novels has made the Harry Potter brand one of the <span>most successful in the world</span>, worth <span>$15 billion</span>, and Rowling the first writer in history to reach the
            <span>$1 billion</span> in concept of profits thanks to their work. In 2005, she was the ninth person with the highest annual income <span>in the world.</span></p>
